label: Gun.js Tests
info: This flow tab contains a number of tests for putting data into a Gun.js database and for retrieving it and/or listening for changes to data.

name: Set vs Put
info:
On a root/top-level document:

* Set with an object creates a single document with 2 properties and random key - Put creates two documents with keys of the object top-level property names.

* Put with a scalar will not do anything because no key is available. Set does work because it creates a random key.

name: Info
info:
## Using `.on` instead of `.map.on`

* returns a SINGLE record for the soul instead of 1 for each document.
* Does NOT output anything when a document is added/changed because the whole soul would need to be changed to trigger an update.

name: ---- PUT/SET at top level of graph (db) ----
---- GET.ONCE - Also triggers on new sub-elements ----
---- How to delete ALL Gun.js data ----
info:
Look for the folder called `_gun`
in your `userDir` folder (normally `~/.node-red`).

You can delete that folder, Gun will recreate it
as needed.

**WARNING**: This will permanently delete _ALL_
locally held data. You probably only want to do
that after you have done some testing.
